Dear `ddccontrol`-people,

launching `gddccontrol`, I was prompted with

> There is no support for your monitor in the database, but ddccontrol
> is using a generic profile for your monitor's manufacturer. Some
> controls may not be supported, or may not work as expected.
> Please update ddccontrol-db, or, if you are already using the latest
> version, please send the output of the following command to
> ddccontrol-users@lists.sourceforge.net:

> `LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddccontrol -p -c -d`

> Thank you.

I have installed ddccontrol-db-git (Arch Linux AUR package), version is 202=
10113.rdd19622-1.

Monitor is an older Philips 220X (as reported by DDC) / 1220I (as printed o=
utside).

Attached you find the output of `LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddccontrol -p -c -d`.

For reference, I have also attached the output of
* `LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddcutil detect`
* `LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddcutil capabilities`
* `LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddcutil vcpinfo`
* `LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddcutil environment`
* `LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddcutil probe`
* `LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddcutil interrogate`


I hope that helps you to add the monitor.

The monitor is controllable by Philips' `SmartControl`-software under windo=
ws, and also `ddcui` can control quite some features.


